<item>
            <title>[LUCENE-3436] Spellchecker &quot;Suggest Mode&quot; Support</title>
                <link>https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/LUCENE-3436</link>
                <project id="12310110" key="LUCENE">Lucene - Core</project>
                        <description>&lt;p&gt;This is a spin-off from &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2585&quot; title=&quot;Context-Sensitive Spelling Suggestions &amp;amp; Collations&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2585&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt;.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Currently o.a.l.s.s.SpellChecker and o.a.l.s.s.DirectSpellChecker support two &quot;Suggest Modes&quot;:&lt;br/&gt;
1. Suggest for terms that are not in the index.&lt;br/&gt;
2. Suggest &quot;more popular&quot; terms.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This issue is to add a third Suggest Mode:&lt;br/&gt;
3. Suggest always.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;This will assist users in developing context-sensitive spell suggestions and/or did-you-mean suggestions.  See &lt;a href=&quot;https://issues.apache.org/jira/browse/SOLR-2585&quot; title=&quot;Context-Sensitive Spelling Suggestions &amp;amp; Collations&quot;&gt;&lt;del&gt;SOLR-2585&lt;/del&gt;&lt;/a&gt; for a full discussion.&lt;/p&gt;

&lt;p&gt;Note that o.a.l.s.s.SpellChecker already can support this functionality, if the user passes in a NULL term &amp;amp; IndexReader.  This, however, is not intutive.  o.a.l.s.s.DirectSpellChecker currently has no support for this third Suggest Mode.&lt;/p&gt;</description>
